 You have GOT to love a compiler that finds things like this,!
The wrong Bit was being tested for mode to detect FULLDUPLEX . 

@TSC21  - this will fix your gcc 9.00 build issue.

When `make px4_sitl_default gazebo`,  declaration error happens
`/home/robin/px4/1.11/Firmware/Tools/sitl_gazebo/src/gazebo_usv_dynamics_plugin.cpp:251:29: error: missing template arguments before ‚ÄòxformV‚Äô
     ignition::math::Matrix4 xformV(vq);
/home/robin/px4/1.11/Firmware/Tools/sitl_gazebo/src/gazebo_usv_dynamics_plugin.cpp:285:15: error: ‚ÄòxformV‚Äô was not declared in this scope
       bpntW = xformV * bpnt;
` 
Looking into gazebo_usv_dynamics_plugin.cpp, it can be seen that for gazebo version >=8.0 (my Gazebo version is 9.13.0) , the declaration is ` ignition::math::Matrix4 xformV(vq);`, which misses template.
`#if GAZEBO_MAJOR_VERSION >= 8
    ignition::math::Matrix4 xformV(vq);
  #else
    ignition::math::Matrix4<double> xformV(vq);
  #endif`
And when I deleted if-else and changed it to `ignition::math::Matrix4<double> xformV(vq);`, `make px4_sitl_default gazebo` passed. So maybe the if-else can be removed.

 - fixes https://github.com/PX4/Firmware/issues/14677
 - updates ecl with https://github.com/PX4/ecl/pull/799

@hyonlim would you be able to test this?
